147.6	Terracotta_Army	Terracotta Army	The Terracotta Army or the "Terra Cotta Warriors and Horses", is a collection of terracotta sculptures depicting the armies of Qin Shi Huang, the first Emperor of China. It is a form of funerary art buried with the emperor in 210â€“209 BC and whose purpose was to protect the emperor in his afterlife, and to make sure that he had people to rule over.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/1_terracotta_army_2011.JPG/250px-1_terracotta_army_2011.JPG
